PhD research, which focused on the political mobilisation of (immigrant origin) Muslims in Europe and on EU and national responses, as well as policies concerning Islam, immigration, and social cohesion. Her main objective during this PDF is to revise her doctoral thesis for publication as an innovative book on the social, political, economic, and legal transformations connected with the growing Islamic presence in the European public sphere and on the ideological challenges that Islam poses to contemporary Europe. &lt;/p> 
&lt;p>During this year she will also complement and expand her interdisciplinary research by examining the conditions and consequences of social exclusion amongst Muslim youth in Europe and will refine specific methodological skills in the social sciences. Awareness of the problems of the present world and of possible solutions should not be limited to the private access of a niche group. Therefore, she intends to pursue publication and to organise research meetings and colloquia at different levels ? targeting academics, policy makers, journalists and the general public. &lt;br />&lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2006-09-06</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2006-01-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>21590</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs/><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs/><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications/><gtr:identifiers><gtr:identifier type="RCUK">PTA-026-27-1002</gtr:identifier></gtr:identifiers><gtr:healthCategories/><gtr:researchActivities/><gtr:researchSubjects><gtr:researchSubject><gtr:id>5D762B83-597E-4E91-B2F7-04CBB955175C</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>0</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>Pol. sci. &amp; internat. studies</gtr:text></gtr:researchSubject></gtr:researchSubjects><gtr:researchTopics><gtr:researchTopic><gtr:id>F7EEE6CD-E283-4BAB-BA5E-70B4B0F1F1A6</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>0</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>Political Science</gtr:text></gtr:researchTopic></gtr:researchTopics><gtr:rcukP